column5:
This week please download R and Rstudio.
Show Diana or Chante your dataset, and
watch the videos as an introduction to Rstudio

Introductions - roll call
Today we will cover R and Rstudio platform.

column4: Introduction to R and R studio

column5: "Nailed it!" What have you learned, attempted, or acomplished

Where do I start?  Diana and I will demonstrate one method, over time you'll have your own process.  We will learn some best practices that are used by other coders as a statrting point for developing your own structure. In groups, you will practice developing an outline for your project and then begin to examine your dataset to identify what needs to be changed.
"Nailed it!" What have you learned, attempted, or acomplished
You will begin to tidy your dataset so that it will be in a format that can be easily used in R.
"Nailed it!" What have you learned, attempted, or acomplished
You will work with your own dataset to try to build code that will allow you to visualize your data using some of the tools that you have learned.
"Nailed it!" What have you learned, attempted, or acomplished
We are going to focus on preparing reproducibile documents.  You've seen several already including the class website.  Our gues presenter TBD.
"Nailed it!" What have you learned, attempted, or acomplished
Try it!  Diana created a Markdown document using the cookie dataset.  You will take that example and build a markdown to describe your dataset.
